Agamemnon spoke. Then he struck Peisander.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0160\uc0\u8232 He knocked him from the chariot to the earth\u8232 with a spear thrust to his chest. He crashed on the ground\u8232 and lay there motionless. Hipplochus jumped out.\u8232 But Agamemnon killed him on the ground.\u8232 His sword sliced away his arms and slashed his head off.\u8232 Then he set the head rolling through the crowd,\u8232 like some round stone. Leaving the bodies there, he charged\u8232 into the line where soldiers\'92 ranks were most confused,\u8232 leading other well-armed Achaeans with him.\u8232 Their men on foot cut down soldiers compelled to flee.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0170\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[150]\u8232 Chariots went at chariots. On the plain, dust clouds arose\u8232 from underneath, kicked up by thundering horses\'92 hooves.\u8232 Men butchered men with bronze. Mighty Agamemnon\u8232 surged on ahead, always killing as he moved,\u8232 shouting out instructions to the Argives.\u8232 Just as destructive fire strikes thick woodland scrub,\u8232 driven in all directions by the swirling wind,\u8232 burning thickets to their roots, so they disappear,\u8232 swallowed up in the inferno\'92s fiery rush,\u8232 that\'92s how the heads of Trojans fell, as they ran off,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0180\u8232 brought down by Agamemnon, son of Atreus.\u8232 Many strong-necked horses in the battle lanes\u8232 rattled past with empty chariots, missing their drivers,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[160]\u8232 excellent charioteers now lying on the ground,\u8232 far more friendly to the vultures than their wives.\
